rComments: Maria was a great professor. She showed immense passion for her subject, and that itself made the course very interesting. Class participation was everything, especially since this was a smaller class in size. In my opinion she spent too much time discussing the readings rather than focusing on the lecture, but otherwise, great class!

Her lectures were like story time. One of my favorite teachers I've had so far in college. homework consists of just short readings every week. Midterm and final are basically entirely off those readings so need to do them to pass (not big deal because the readings are easy).

This teacher is very hard her accent makes the class hard to follow and her slides are all over the place i would advise students not to take her class i regret being in this class but i need it in order to graduate overall i am disappointed in her abilities as a teacher because she is disorganized and her midterm is dumb

Professor Diaz, while seeming to have the best of intentions, left me totally frustrated with her disorganization this past quarter. Test instructions, last minute assignments and changes to the schedule had me feeling constantly on edge and discouraged. This quarter may have been a fluke, however i would not take another class with this professor.

Maria was the first teacher I've ever had, including high school, that I just did not like. She was horribly rude to students, especially in the fiasco that occurred with our midterm, wherein she accidentally posted the wrong questions for take-home essays, and then penalized people for her own mistakes. She's terrible as a teacher and a person.

She is great at what she teaches and really knows her history. Maria Elena shows bias against anyone who looks "different". She definitely has favorites in the class and is not afraid to show it. Incredibly rude and shows no regard for anyone but herself.

I've taken almost every class she has taught at UCSC and I have loved all her classes. Honestly, her expectations of her students aren't demanding and her work load is more tedious than difficult. But she is passionate about the subject she teaches and is extremely helpful when you see her at office hours.

I really liked Maria. I think her class/work load/grading policy is fair for an upper div hist course. Not super easy, but manageable. She's understanding and will help you out as much as she can, but she's far from a push over. My advice: always do the key readings, work hard on the essays, participate in class, and go to office hours!

It's so clear how passionate Dr Diaz is about Latin American History, she really knows her stuff. The class itself wasn't that bad. We had to buy about 5 books, which weren't too bad to read. She did assign a lot of essays however, but if you read the books, they were rather easy. The midterm and final requires a lot of studying. Do the work=A.

I LOVED this class. Maria is extremely passionate about this subject, and it is taught in a small classroom setting where students do the readings then come in for a discussion-like lecture. I loved the reading materials (except the religious texts) and it was overall a somewhat easy class. Do the readings, and you will excel. +she will like you.

This class was really boring. Attendance is mandatory. Her work load was based on an upper div. Sh etook her lectures too seriously even though she was very confusing. You pretty much have to write a paper on a different book each week and her test are not hard but she makes you write 6 essays in a regular class time. DONT TAKE
Meh. Expected more from this class.

I absolutely loved Maria. She is not the easiest grader, but I found her class very interesting. I would not call her a hard teacher, and she definitely is passionate about what she teaches. Lectures can be a little boring but overall the class is very intriguing.

really bad teacher. Not helpful atall. Very rude and mean. Too much work.very hard grader. And changes the schedule all the time..u cant keep up and get confused about what is due when!!!! bad teacher.

it is so hard to actually understand what she is trying to say and repeats really insignificant parts of the lecture and then skips over really important parts.gives ridiculously long assignments that you have to do in a VERY short amount of time.easy but a lot of work. really nice. takes attendance. no breaks.
Maria is beautiful! She has the cutest accent. Not an easy teacher but nice and a fair grader.

Was my official faculty advisor, though I didn't really see much of her.  The class was very well done and I agree with the above comment that she's way easier than these comments make her out to be.  Don't slack off and actually go to class!  I didn't go to class and had to take the extra class, which wasn't particularly hard anyway.

She is horribly annoying and talks AT the class for an hour and forty five minutes if not more without a break. She often goes off on tangents that have nothing to do with the material at hand. She is obviously very educated but lacks teaching skills across all levels. The sound of her voice saying "and then" makes me want to cry.
She is a nice person but she lacks over all teaching abilities. Her lectures do not have coherence and resemble rants. Class is easy, but not memorable

She is a really good teacher, and gives A LOT of important information. Notes are really important, she gives study guides but all the information comes from your own notes. Her lecturing is boring, kind of dry, but she tells interesting information. Pretty easy class: do the reading, speak in section, have good notes and you can easily pass.

I was very interested colonialism and the Caribbean before taking this class.  However, Diaz's lectures were often boring and dry which seemed to suck the life out of the material.  Has a strict attendence policy so I wouldn't recommend her if you like to skip class occassionally. More than 2 absences and you have to take an additional test.

People who complain about this class being hard are slackers.  This class is so so so easy!  I didn't do much of anything and I got a big fat A.  She is a very nice lady and is very interesting to talk to.  Her accent is cool, she likes feedback and she cares about her students.  Her lectures can go on a tangent, but its like storytime ! Take her!
She's very passionate about her lectures and provides a lot of visual material.  Sometimes she starts lecturing at mach speed and you need to tell her to slow down.
This class is so boring. She is also so unclear and confusing.  She is also kind of mean. Gives pop quizzes and takes attendance. Very boring books. Not super hard but really bad class
This prof. is very boring. Her lectures are scattered and horrible to sit through. The books for the class were also very boring. She takes attendence. I still don't have an eval. over a year later.

Dr. Diaz is one of the best professors at UCSC! She cares about her students, and gives thorough feedback.  If you want a good narrative eval, then don't turn in crap for your papers!  Knows her area (Latin America) VERY well.
The class is extremely boring and very unclear.  You can get a decent grade by doing the reading but class is awful and she takes attendance.  She was always late and had no organization.
